title: Mountain Pointe tops Desert Vista in big rivalry game
text:
Mountain Pointe tops Desert Vista in big rivalry game The 'Tukee bowl goes to Mountain Pointe. Post to Facebook Mountain Pointe tops Desert Vista in big rivalry game The 'Tukee bowl goes to Mountain Pointe.   12news.com: http://12ne.ws/1RjyIOx   Join the Conversation To   Mountain Pointe tops Desert Vista in big rivalry game Elaine Wilson, 12 Sports 11:18 p.m. MST October 1, 2015 The 'Tukee bowl goes to Mountain Pointe. Desert Vista threw 3 interceptions, loses Ahwatukee Bowl at home. (Photo: 12 Sports) CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE Desert Vista throws 3 interceptions, loses Ahwatukee Bowl at home. KPNX 
The Ahwatukee Bowl was a dramatic one, with Mountain Pointe securing the win in the fourth quarter with a score of 28-14. 
But for Mountain Pointe quarterback Jack Smith, the 'Tukee Bowl was just like any other week on the field. 
"To me, because I didn't grow up here, I didn't know anything about it. It felt like any other game." 
Mountain Pointe head coach Norris Vaughn echoed similar feelings. 
"They're a good group of kids. They're in our neighborhood, we love them." 
Desert Vista quarterback Nick Thomas threw three interceptions on the night, two of which became touchdowns later in the drive. The third and final interception came with less than three minutes on the clock. 
Desert Vista will face Red Mountain next week while undefeated Mountain Pointe will face Desert Ridge. Read or Share this story: http://12ne.ws/1RjyIOx TOP VIDEOS
